Bob Hewitt was sentenced to six years in prison in 2015 after he was convicted of raping and sexually assaulting three youths. JOHANNESBURG - The Correctional Supervision and Parole Review Board has set aside the parole of former tennis coach Bob Hewitt.
The 79-year-old was sentenced to six years in prison in 2015 after he was convicted of raping and sexually assaulting three youths. READ: Bob Hewitt's release on parole suspended He had coached all three women in the 1980s and 1990s. The department says proper procedures were not followed by the parole board when considering Hewitt's application. READ: Bob Hewitt - appeal denied, sent to jail He was scheduled to be released on 23 September. The decision means he will remain behind bars.